de.team33.libs.exceptional.v3

Class BiDisclosure<R extends RuntimeException,X extends Throwable,Y extends Throwable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.team33.libs.exceptional.v3.BiDisclosure<R,X,Y>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - The specific type of enclosing RuntimeExceptions to be looked at.
    X - The first specific type of exceptions to be disclosed.
    Y - The other specific type of exceptions to be disclosed.

    public final class BiDisclosure<R extends RuntimeException,X extends Throwable,Y extends Throwable>
extends Object

    A tool to disclose two specific types of (typically checked) exceptions wrapped by (cause of) a specific type of RuntimeExceptions.

    See Also:
    Disclosing.on(Class), Disclosing.disclose(Class, Class), Disclosing.disclose(Class, Class, Consumer)

      • run

        public final void run(Runnable runnable)
               throws X extends Throwable,
                      Y extends Throwable
        Immediately executes a Runnable.
        Throws:
        X - if the Runnable causes a RuntimeException of type <R>, which in turn is caused by an exception of type <X>.
        Y - if the Runnable causes a RuntimeException of type <R>, which in turn is caused by an exception of type <Y>.
        R - if the Runnable causes a RuntimeException of type <R>, which is NOT caused by an exception of type <X> or <Y>.
        X extends Throwable
